definition.value: A vasopressin V2 receptor antagonist that has been shown to improve hyponatremia in patients with cirrhosis, congestive heart failure, and syndrome of inappropriate antidiuresis.
A vernolate that is the conjugate base of (-)-vernolic acid, resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group; Major species at pH 7.3.
A composition-only glycan consisting of four hexosyl groups, one acetaminohexosyl group and two 6-deoxyhexosyl groups (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex4 HexNAc1 dHex2.
A composition-only glycan consisting of six hexosyl groups, four acetaminohexosyl groups and one 6-deoxyhexosyl group (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex6 HexNAc4 dHex1.
A class of diuretics which promote aquaresis (the excretion of water without electrolyte loss).

A protein that lacks a well defined tertiary structure. These proteins are flexible, non-compact (extended) and have little or no ordered secondary structure under physiological conditions. They are involved in several cellular processes (E.g. signalling, targeting and DNA binding) and may play important roles in the development of cancer and amyloidotic diseases.

A member of the class of chromenes that is 4H-chromene substituted by amino, cyano, 2-methoxyphenyl, and dimethylamino groups at positions 2, 3, 4 and 7, respectively. It exhibits anti-angiogenic activity.
A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)-mevalonolactone and (S)-mevalonolactone.
A drug used to treat myopathy.
A negatively charged group obtained by removal of a proton from the phosphate group of queuosine 5'-phosphate residue. Major species at pH 7.3.
Rhodoquinone (RQ) is a modified ubiquinone, where the methoxyl group in position 3 is replaced by an amino group.
An octadecenoate that is the conjugate base of (10E)-octadecenoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 10-hydroxypalmitic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
An octadecadienoate that is the conjugate base of (5Z,8Z)-octadecadienoic acid, resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group; Major species at pH 7.3.
